image.altText: Adam Watt portrait photo

props.synopsis: Inside the jail courtyard Adam felt out of place. He had just signed a media deal and was looking forward to stepping into the limelight until it all came crashing down. At the top of his list is one man, a corrupt cop charged with drug offences.

title.children: In prison and out of his depth, one man started investigating a corrupt cop

image.altText: Front of a healthcare outlet.

props.synopsis: The Department of Health has been told to investigate price-gouging practices by health insurers after one fund ignored a warning from the health minister to stop exploiting a loophole to increase prices above the government-approved cap.

title.children: Health minister orders urgent investigation of HCF price hike

image.altText: Peter Dutton

props.synopsis: The first week of the official election campaign is well underway as both leaders take to the radio and another Chinese ship floats past Australia.

image.altText: A woman in a blue jacket

props.synopsis: A Paris court has convicted French far-right leader Marine Le Pen of embezzling money from the European parliament.

title.children: Breaking: French far-right leader Marine Le Pen convicted in embezzlement trial

image.altText: President Donald Trump arrives on Air Force One at Palm Beach International Airport, Friday, March 28

props.synopsis: Under the US constitution no president can hold government more than twice, but Mr Trump tells US media there are "methods" that he could use to secure a third term.

title.children: Trump says he's 'not joking' about trying to secure third presidential term

image.altText: A Buddhist monk walks near a collapsed pagoda.

props.synopsis: After an earthquake in Myanmar, more than 1,700 people are dead, rescue crews are searching the rubble of a skyscraper in Bangkok, and aid is struggling to reach people in need of medical care, food and water.

image.altText: People at voting boots.

image.altText: Man holding sign on green lawn

image.altText: Gout Gout crouches after 200m at Maurie Plant Meet.

image.altText: Drone shot of a large green park surrounded by houses with the ocean in the background.

image.altText: Woman and daughter press their foreheads together in a smiling pose

image.altText: organic green vegetables, sugar cubes, marshmallow, pills and blood sugar test set on blue background

image.altText: Eight Race Around the World contestants posing for a group shot, blue background.

image.altText: A close up photo of Prince Harry's face

image.altText: Ben Roberts-Smith in a suit and tie

image.altText: Australian Electoral Commission staff in purple vests sit at a table counting votes as other people in green vests watch over.

image.altText: Two people in white forensic outfits covering their entire body observing the inside of a home. One is taking a photo inside.

image.altText: A composite image of Mark Haines with railway tracks.

image.altText: A man celebrates during a rugby league match

image.altText: German startup Isar Aerospace explodes after falling down in Norway

image.altText: Nicola Spurrier is dressed in a multi-coloured jacket as she addresses the media

image.altText: Outline of a stadium as seen from Hobart's cenotaph

image.altText: A woman with long blonde hair sits in an armchair and looks over her right shoulder at a window.

image.altText: Aerial shot of a mine and buildings

image.altText: Richard Norton smiling at camera in a grey shirt, in front of a white hallway.

image.altText: a man being wheeled by paramedics outside court

image.altText: A yellow ant.
